{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"Since 2009, the world has been stuck"},{"time":4680,"text":"on a single narrative\naround a coming global food crisis"},{"time":9840,"text":"and what we need to do to avoid it."},{"time":13040,"text":"How do we feed\nnine billion people by 2050?"},{"time":18440,"text":"Every conference, podcast\nand dialogue around global food security"},{"time":23080,"text":"starts with this question"},{"time":24800,"text":"and goes on to answer it"},{"time":26560,"text":"by saying we need to produce\n70 percent more food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33160,"text":"The 2050 narrative started to evolve"},{"time":36000,"text":"shortly after global food prices\nhit all-time highs in 2008."},{"time":41440,"text":"People were suffering and struggling,"},{"time":44240,"text":"governments and world leaders"},{"time":45800,"text":"needed to show us\nthat they were paying attention"},{"time":48440,"text":"and were working to solve it."},{"time":51760,"text":"The thing is, 2050\nis so far into the future"},{"time":55560,"text":"that we can't even relate to it,"},{"time":58280,"text":"and more importantly,"},{"time":60040,"text":"if we keep doing what we're doing,"},{"time":62320,"text":"it's going to hit us\na lot sooner than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66080,"text":"I believe we need to ask\na different question."},{"time":70280,"text":"The answer to that question"},{"time":72640,"text":"needs to be framed differently."},{"time":77120,"text":"If we can reframe the old narrative"},{"time":79880,"text":"and replace it with new numbers"},{"time":82360,"text":"that tell us a more complete pictures,"},{"time":85720,"text":"numbers that everyone can understand"},{"time":88920,"text":"and relate to,"},{"time":91320,"text":"we can avoid the crisis altogether."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96560,"text":"I was a commodities trader in my past life"},{"time":99440,"text":"and one of the things\nthat I learned trading"},{"time":101640,"text":"is that every market has a tipping point,"},{"time":105360,"text":"the point at which\nchange occurs so rapidly"},{"time":108960,"text":"that it impacts the world"},{"time":110840,"text":"and things change forever."},{"time":114080,"text":"Think of the last financial crisis,"},{"time":117800,"text":"or the dot-com crash."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120920,"text":"So here's my concern."},{"time":124760,"text":"We could have a tipping point"},{"time":126840,"text":"in global food and agriculture"},{"time":129000,"text":"if surging demand"},{"time":130919,"text":"surpasses the agricultural system's\nstructural capacity to produce food."},{"time":138240,"text":"This means at this point supply\ncan no longer keep up with demand"},{"time":143000,"text":"despite exploding prices,"},{"time":145280,"text":"unless we can commit\nto some type of structural change."},{"time":150560,"text":"This time around,"},{"time":152360,"text":"it won't be about stock markets and money."},{"time":154960,"text":"It's about people."},{"time":156360,"text":"People could starve\nand governments may fall."},{"time":161200,"text":"This question of at what point\ndoes supply struggle"},{"time":165760,"text":"to keep up with surging demand"},{"time":167440,"text":"is one that started off as an interest\nfor me while I was trading"},{"time":171120,"text":"and became an absolute obsession."},{"time":173920,"text":"It went from interest to obsession"},{"time":176880,"text":"when I realized through my research\nhow broken the system was"},{"time":180560,"text":"and how very little data was being used\nto make such critical decisions."},{"time":185640,"text":"That's the point I decided to walk away\nfrom a career on Wall Street"},{"time":189920,"text":"and start an entrepreneurial journey"},{"time":192440,"text":"to start Gro Intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194880,"text":"At Gro, we focus on bringing this data"},{"time":198400,"text":"and doing the work to make it actionable,"},{"time":200680,"text":"to empower decision-makers at every level."},{"time":204880,"text":"But doing this work,"},{"time":206520,"text":"we also realized that the world,"},{"time":208800,"text":"not just world leaders,"},{"time":210480,"text":"but businesses and citizens\nlike every single person in this room,"},{"time":214760,"text":"lacked an actionable guide"},{"time":217760,"text":"on how we can avoid\na coming global food security crisis."},{"time":222400,"text":"And so we built a model,"},{"time":224440,"text":"leveraging the petabytes\nof data we sit on,"},{"time":227360,"text":"and we solved for the tipping point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230560,"text":"Now, no one knows\nwe've been working on this problem"},{"time":234200,"text":"and this is the first time\nthat I'm sharing what we discovered."},{"time":240200,"text":"We discovered that the tipping point\nis actually a decade from now."},{"time":246280,"text":"We discovered that the world"},{"time":248640,"text":"will be short 214 trillion calories"},{"time":254960,"text":"by 2027."},{"time":257440,"text":"The world is not in a position\nto fill this gap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262400,"text":"Now, you'll notice"},{"time":264960,"text":"that the way I'm framing this\nis different from how I started,"},{"time":269280,"text":"and that's intentional, because until now"},{"time":271440,"text":"this problem has been\nquantified using mass:"},{"time":274680,"text":"think kilograms, tons, hectograms,"},{"time":277520,"text":"whatever your unit of choice is in mass."},{"time":280280,"text":"Why do we talk about food\nin terms of weight?"},{"time":283360,"text":"Because it's easy."},{"time":284800,"text":"We can look at a photograph\nand determine tonnage on a ship"},{"time":288320,"text":"by using a simple pocket calculator."},{"time":290600,"text":"We can weigh trucks,\nairplanes and oxcarts."},{"time":293880,"text":"But what we care about\nin food is nutritional value."},{"time":299040,"text":"Not all foods are created equal,"},{"time":302200,"text":"even if they weigh the same."},{"time":304920,"text":"This I learned firsthand"},{"time":307400,"text":"when I moved from Ethiopia\nto the US for university."},{"time":311200,"text":"Upon my return back home,"},{"time":313360,"text":"my father, who was so excited to see me,"},{"time":316600,"text":"greeted me by asking why I was fat."},{"time":320960,"text":"Now, turns out that eating"},{"time":326760,"text":"approximately the same amount of food\nas I did in Ethiopia, but in America,"},{"time":331640,"text":"had actually lent\na certain fullness to my figure."},{"time":336760,"text":"This is why we should care about calories,"},{"time":340880,"text":"not about mass."},{"time":342560,"text":"It is calories which sustain us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346880,"text":"So 214 trillion calories\nis a very large number,"},{"time":352720,"text":"and not even the most dedicated of us"},{"time":355880,"text":"think in the hundreds\nof trillions of calories."},{"time":358840,"text":"So let me break this down differently."},{"time":361880,"text":"An alternative way to think about this"},{"time":365240,"text":"is to think about it in Big Macs."},{"time":368120,"text":"214 trillion calories."},{"time":370760,"text":"A single Big Mac has 563 calories."},{"time":374000,"text":"That means the world will be short\n379 billion Big Macs in 2027."},{"time":380240,"text":"That is more Big Macs\nthan McDonald's has ever produced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385960,"text":"So how did we get\nto these numbers in the first place?"},{"time":390040,"text":"They're not made up."},{"time":392400,"text":"This map shows you\nwhere the world was 40 years ago."},{"time":397240,"text":"It shows you net calorie gaps\nin every country in the world."},{"time":401280,"text":"Now, simply put,"},{"time":402760,"text":"this is just calories\nconsumed in that country"},{"time":405800,"text":"minus calories produced\nin that same country."},{"time":408880,"text":"This is not a statement\non malnutrition or anything else."},{"time":411680,"text":"It's simply saying how many calories\nare consumed in a single year"},{"time":415720,"text":"minus how many are produced."},{"time":417600,"text":"Blue countries are net calorie exporters,"},{"time":421000,"text":"or self-sufficient."},{"time":422400,"text":"They have some in storage for a rainy day."},{"time":425080,"text":"Red countries are net calorie importers."},{"time":427920,"text":"The deeper, the brighter the red,"},{"time":429880,"text":"the more you're importing."},{"time":432200,"text":"40 years ago, such few countries\nwere net exporters of calories,"},{"time":436680,"text":"I could count them with one hand."},{"time":439360,"text":"Most of the African continent,"},{"time":441480,"text":"Europe, most of Asia,"},{"time":444120,"text":"South America excluding Argentina,"},{"time":446160,"text":"were all net importers of calories."},{"time":448560,"text":"And what's surprising is that China\nused to actually be food self-sufficient."},{"time":452680,"text":"India was a big net importer of calories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457080,"text":"40 years later, this is today."},{"time":459960,"text":"You can see the drastic transformation\nthat's occurred in the world."},{"time":464040,"text":"Brazil has emerged\nas an agricultural powerhouse."},{"time":467560,"text":"Europe is dominant in global agriculture."},{"time":470840,"text":"India has actually flipped\nfrom red to blue."},{"time":473840,"text":"It's become food self-sufficient."},{"time":476120,"text":"And China went from that light blue"},{"time":478600,"text":"to the brightest red\nthat you see on this map."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482280,"text":"How did we get here? What happened?"},{"time":485960,"text":"So this chart shows you India and Africa."},{"time":489440,"text":"Blue line is India, red line is Africa."},{"time":492440,"text":"How is it that two regions\nthat started off so similarly"},{"time":496600,"text":"in such similar trajectories"},{"time":498760,"text":"take such different paths?"},{"time":500920,"text":"India had a green revolution."},{"time":504000,"text":"Not a single African country\nhad a green revolution."},{"time":508120,"text":"The net outcome?"},{"time":509360,"text":"India is food self-sufficient"},{"time":511080,"text":"and in the past decade\nhas actually been exporting calories."},{"time":514480,"text":"The African continent now imports\nover 300 trillion calories a year."},{"time":519280,"text":"Then we add China, the green line."},{"time":523600,"text":"Remember the switch\nfrom the blue to the bright red?"},{"time":527120,"text":"What happened and when did it happen?"},{"time":530200,"text":"China seemed to be\non a very similar path to India"},{"time":533080,"text":"until the start of the 21st century,"},{"time":535880,"text":"where it suddenly flipped."},{"time":538400,"text":"A young and growing population"},{"time":540440,"text":"combined with significant economic growth"},{"time":543560,"text":"made its mark with a big bang"},{"time":546000,"text":"and no one in the markets saw it coming."},{"time":549520,"text":"This flip was everything\nto global agricultural markets."},{"time":553280,"text":"Luckily now, South America"},{"time":556120,"text":"was starting to boom\nat the same time as China's rise,"},{"time":561360,"text":"and so therefore, supply and demand\nwere still somewhat balanced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566320,"text":"So the question becomes,"},{"time":568640,"text":"where do we go from here?"},{"time":571800,"text":"Oddly enough,"},{"time":573360,"text":"it's not a new story,"},{"time":575800,"text":"except this time\nit's not just a story of China."},{"time":579200,"text":"It's a continuation of China,"},{"time":581600,"text":"an amplification of Africa"},{"time":583720,"text":"and a paradigm shift in India."},{"time":586600,"text":"By 2023,"},{"time":589000,"text":"Africa's population is forecasted\nto overtake that of India's and China's."},{"time":594080,"text":"By 2023, these three regions combined"},{"time":596760,"text":"will make up over half\nthe world's population."},{"time":601400,"text":"This crossover point starts to present\nreally interesting challenges"},{"time":605440,"text":"for global food security."},{"time":607200,"text":"And a few years later,\nwe're hit hard with that reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612120,"text":"What does the world look like in 10 years?"},{"time":617120,"text":"So far, as I mentioned,\nIndia has been food self-sufficient."},{"time":621040,"text":"Most forecasters predict\nthat this will continue."},{"time":625200,"text":"We disagree."},{"time":627160,"text":"India will soon become\na net importer of calories."},{"time":631320,"text":"This will be driven both by the fact"},{"time":633600,"text":"that demand is growing\nfrom a population growth standpoint"},{"time":637120,"text":"plus economic growth."},{"time":638400,"text":"It will be driven by both."},{"time":639680,"text":"And even if you have\noptimistic assumptions"},{"time":642400,"text":"around production growth,"},{"time":644320,"text":"it will make that slight flip."},{"time":646960,"text":"That slight flip\ncan have huge implications."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651800,"text":"Next, Africa will continue\nto be a net importer of calories,"},{"time":656360,"text":"again driven by population growth\nand economic growth."},{"time":660120,"text":"This is again assuming optimistic\nproduction growth assumptions."},{"time":664040,"text":"Then China,"},{"time":665480,"text":"where population is flattening out,"},{"time":668080,"text":"calorie consumption will explode"},{"time":670080,"text":"because the types of calories consumed"},{"time":673120,"text":"are also starting to be\nhigher-calorie-content foods."},{"time":677600,"text":"And so therefore,"},{"time":679360,"text":"these three regions combined"},{"time":681240,"text":"start to present a really interesting\nchallenge for the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684560,"text":"Until now, countries with calorie deficits"},{"time":688680,"text":"have been able to meet these deficits"},{"time":691280,"text":"by importing from surplus regions."},{"time":693720,"text":"By surplus regions, I'm talking about"},{"time":696560,"text":"North America, South America and Europe."},{"time":699720,"text":"This line chart over here shows you"},{"time":702160,"text":"the growth and the projected growth\nover the next decade of production"},{"time":706480,"text":"from North America,\nSouth America and Europe."},{"time":708800,"text":"What it doesn't show you"},{"time":710240,"text":"is that most of this growth is actually\ngoing to come from South America."},{"time":714640,"text":"And most of this growth"},{"time":716080,"text":"is going to come\nat the huge cost of deforestation."},{"time":722240,"text":"And so when you look\nat the combined demand increase"},{"time":726040,"text":"coming from India, China\nand the African continent,"},{"time":730200,"text":"and look at it versus\nthe combined increase in production"},{"time":733040,"text":"coming from India,\nChina, the African continent,"},{"time":735840,"text":"North America, South America and Europe,"},{"time":739280,"text":"you are left with\na 214-trillion-calorie deficit,"},{"time":744720,"text":"one we can't produce."},{"time":746480,"text":"And this, by the way, is actually assuming\nwe take all the extra calories"},{"time":750440,"text":"produced in North America,\nSouth America and Europe"},{"time":753880,"text":"and export them solely\nto India, China and Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759200,"text":"What I just presented to you\nis a vision of an impossible world."},{"time":763520,"text":"We can do something to change that."},{"time":766400,"text":"We can change consumption patterns,"},{"time":768720,"text":"we can reduce food waste,"},{"time":771000,"text":"or we can make a bold commitment"},{"time":774240,"text":"to increasing yields exponentially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777720,"text":"Now, I'm not going to go into discussing"},{"time":779880,"text":"changing consumption patterns\nor reducing food waste,"},{"time":782400,"text":"because those conversations\nhave been going on for some time now."},{"time":785480,"text":"Nothing has happened."},{"time":786720,"text":"Nothing has happened\nbecause those arguments"},{"time":790200,"text":"ask the surplus regions\nto change their behavior"},{"time":793160,"text":"on behalf of deficit regions."},{"time":796880,"text":"Waiting for others\nto change their behavior"},{"time":799480,"text":"on your behalf, for your survival,"},{"time":802000,"text":"is a terrible idea."},{"time":803520,"text":"It's unproductive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805560,"text":"So I'd like to suggest an alternative\nthat comes from the red regions."},{"time":811960,"text":"China, India, Africa."},{"time":814360,"text":"China is constrained in terms\nof how much more land it actually has"},{"time":817680,"text":"available for agriculture,"},{"time":819240,"text":"and it has massive\nwater resource availability issues."},{"time":823040,"text":"So the answer really lies\nin India and in Africa."},{"time":827840,"text":"India has some upside\nin terms of potential yield increases."},{"time":832800,"text":"Now this is the gap\nbetween its current yield"},{"time":835400,"text":"and the theoretical\nmaximum yield it can achieve."},{"time":839720,"text":"It has some unfarmed\narable land remaining, but not much,"},{"time":842960,"text":"India is quite land-constrained."},{"time":846240,"text":"Now, the African continent,\non the other hand,"},{"time":848920,"text":"has vast amounts of arable land remaining"},{"time":852240,"text":"and significant\nupside potential in yields."},{"time":856080,"text":"Somewhat simplified picture here,"},{"time":858200,"text":"but if you look at sub-Saharan\nAfrican yields in corn today,"},{"time":863240,"text":"they are where North American\nyields were in 1940."},{"time":868600,"text":"We don't have 70-plus years\nto figure this out,"},{"time":872360,"text":"so it means we need to try something new"},{"time":874920,"text":"and we need to try something different."},{"time":878400,"text":"The solution starts with reforms."},{"time":881880,"text":"We need to reform and commercialize"},{"time":885880,"text":"the agricultural industries in Africa"},{"time":888440,"text":"and in India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890320,"text":"Now, by commercialization --"},{"time":892480,"text":"commercialization is not\nabout commercial farming alone."},{"time":895640,"text":"Commercialization is about leveraging data"},{"time":898240,"text":"to craft better policies,"},{"time":900560,"text":"to improve infrastructure,"},{"time":902200,"text":"to lower the transportation costs"},{"time":904080,"text":"and to completely reform\nbanking and insurance industries."},{"time":908360,"text":"Commercialization\nis about taking agriculture"},{"time":911480,"text":"from too risky an endeavor\nto one where fortunes can be made."},{"time":915600,"text":"Commercialization\nis not about just farmers."},{"time":918880,"text":"Commercialization is about\nthe entire agricultural system."},{"time":924840,"text":"But commercialization\nalso means confronting the fact"},{"time":928920,"text":"that we can no longer place\nthe burden of growth"},{"time":932360,"text":"on small-scale farmers alone,"},{"time":936600,"text":"and accepting that commercial farms\nand the introduction of commercial farms"},{"time":941880,"text":"could provide certain economies of scale"},{"time":944600,"text":"that even small-scale\nfarmers can leverage."},{"time":948040,"text":"It is not about small-scale farming\nor commercial agriculture,"},{"time":952040,"text":"or big agriculture."},{"time":953920,"text":"We can create the first successful models\nof the coexistence and success"},{"time":959200,"text":"of small-scale farming\nalongside commercial agriculture."},{"time":963000,"text":"This is because, for the first time ever,"},{"time":966040,"text":"the most critical tool\nfor success in the industry --"},{"time":969800,"text":"data and knowledge --"},{"time":971320,"text":"is becoming cheaper by the day."},{"time":974720,"text":"And very soon, it won't matter\nhow much money you have"},{"time":978160,"text":"or how big you are"},{"time":979640,"text":"to make optimal decisions\nand maximize probability of success"},{"time":983960,"text":"in reaching your intended goal."},{"time":987320,"text":"Companies like Gro are working\nreally hard to make this a reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991600,"text":"So if we can commit\nto this new, bold initiative,"},{"time":996200,"text":"to this new, bold change,"},{"time":998240,"text":"not only can we solve\nthe 214-trillion gap that I talked about,"},{"time":1003680,"text":"but we can actually set the world\non a whole new path."},{"time":1006960,"text":"India can remain food self-sufficient"},{"time":1011080,"text":"and Africa can emerge\nas the world's next dark blue region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017240,"text":"The new question is,"},{"time":1019480,"text":"how do we produce 214 trillion calories"},{"time":1023640,"text":"to feed 8.3 billion people by 2027?"},{"time":1028760,"text":"We have the solution."},{"time":1030960,"text":"We just need to act on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033520,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034760,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}